    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/podcast-marks-international-human-rights-day--2"/>
    <title>Podcast marks International Human Rights Day</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The fight against torture has been a priority for the British Government for many years. We make clear time and time again that torture is an abhorrent, unjustifiable violation of human rights and human dignity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This audio download is introduced by the Louise de Sousa, head of the Foreign Office Human Rights and Democracy Department.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;During the podcast, we hear from Kolbassia Haoussou, a survivor of torture and Coordinator of &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.freedomfromtorture.org/feature/survivors_speak_out/5993" title="Survivor Speak OUT.com"&gt;Survivor Speak OUT.com&lt;/a&gt;, Alex Wilks Senior Programme Lawyer at the &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.ibanet.org/IBAHRI.aspx" title="International Bar Association Human Rights Institute"&gt;International Bar Association Human Rights Institute&lt;/a&gt;, and Nick Hardwick CBE, who has been Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector of Prisons since 2010.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The podcast is available to download via &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/news/social-media/podcasts" title="FCO website"&gt;our website&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a rel="external" href="https://itunes.apple.com/gb/podcast/human-rights/id462779772" title="iTunes"&gt;iTunes&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="further-information"&gt;Further information&lt;/h3&gt;

