    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/minister-for-burma-welcomes-aung-san-suu-kyi-s-joint-statement-on-rakhine-state-with-burmese-parliamentarians"/>
    <title>Minister for Burma welcomes Aung San Suu Kyi’s joint statement on Rakhine state with Burmese parliamentarians</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Following Aung San Suu Kyi’s joint statement on Rakhine state with Burmese parliamentarians, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office Minister of State Rt Hon Hugo Swire MP said:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;“I welcome the joint statement on the situation in Rakhine State from Burma’s Parliamentary Committee on Rule of Law, chaired by Daw Aung San Suu Kyi and ethnic MPs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;“I echo the statement’s calls for increased security, respect for human rights regardless of ethnic group or religion, accountability for crimes committed, and increased humanitarian support. I also welcome its call for the issue of citizenship to be looked at urgently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;“The UK continues to stand beside those in Burma working for freedom and democracy.”&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.fco.gov.uk/resources/en/jpg/News/711631982/October/human-trafficking-large1"&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
